  description:
   { fr:
      'Quote Colors est une extension pour Thunderbird ou SeaMonkey.\n\nElle permet de choisir les couleurs du texte et du fond pour les différents niveaux de citation des messages (mail/news), que ce soit à l\'écran ou une fois imprimés. Il est possible d\'indiquer 5 couleurs de niveau de citation.\nVous pouvez choisir entre deux styles de citation : le style graphique, avec des barres de couleurs encadrant les paragraphes cités (style par défaut), ou bien le style standard où chaque ligne citée est précédée d\'une ou de plusieurs fois le caractère "&gt;". En mode graphique, vous pouvez ajuster la couleur, la position et le style des barres.\n\nCette extension permet enfin d\'ajuster certaines couleurs des messages : le texte, le fond, les liens ou encore la signature.',
     de:
      'Quote Colors ist ein Add-on für Thunderbird und die E-Mail &amp; Newsgruppen-Komponente von SeaMonkey.\n\nEs ermöglicht Ihnen, unterschiedlichen Zitatebenen in E-Mails und Newsgruppenbeiträgen verschiedene Text- und Hintergrundfarben zuzuweisen, welche beim lesen oder drucken angewendet werden. Fünf Zitatebenen können hierbei mit individuellen Farben belegt werden.\nWeiterhin können Sie zwischen zwei Anzeigemodi für Zitate wählen: grafischer Zitiermodus mit gefärbten Balken um die zitierten Absätze (Standard) und dem traditionellen Zitieren im Klartextmodus, in welchem jede zitierte Zeile mit einem oder mehreren „&gt;“ Zeichen eingeleitet wird. Im grafischen Zitiermodus sind die Farbe, Position und Stil der Balken einstellbar.\n\nZusätzlich bietet dieses Add-on einige grundlegende Einstellungen zur Darstellung von Nachrichten wie Text-, Hintergrund-, Link- und Signaturfarben.',
     'en-US':
      'Quote Colors is an add-on for Thunderbird and the mail &amp; newsgroup client of SeaMonkey.\n\nIt allows you to assign text and background colors to different quote levels which are applied when reading or printing mail/news messages. Five quote levels can be configured with distinct colors.\nYou can choose between two quoting display modes: graphical quoting with colored bars around quoted paragraphs (default), and traditional plain text quoting where each quoted line starts with one or more "&gt;" characters. In graphical quoting, the color, position and style of the bars is adjustable.\n\nAdditionally, this add-on enables you to set up some basic message display options such as text, background, link and signature colors.',
     da:
      'Quote Colors er en tilføjelse til Thunderbird og SeaMonkeys mail &amp; nyhedsgruppeklient.\n\nDen giver dig mulighed for, at tildele tekst- og baggrundsfarve for forskellige citatniveauer, der anvendes ved læsning eller udskrivning mail/news-meddelelser.\nDu kan vælge mellem to citatvisningsmåder: grafisk citering med farvede bjælker om citerede afsnit (standard), og traditionel citering i ren tekst, hvor hver citeret linje starter med en eller flere "&gt;"-tegn. I grafisk citering er det muligt, at tilpasse bjælkernes farve, position og stil.\n\nDenne tilføjelse giver dig også mulighed for, at lave nogle grundlæggende visningsindstillinger så som baggrunds-, link- og signaturfarver.',
     ja:
      'Quote Colors は Thunderbird と SeaMonkey のメールクライアント用のアドオンです。\n\nメッセージの表示時や印刷時、引用文のテキスト色と背景色を階層ごとに選択できます。引用文の色は 5 階層まで設定できます。\n引用文の表示モードを次のどちらかから選ぶことができます: 段落が色付きの境界線で装飾されたグラフィカルな引用 (デフォルト)、または各段落が "&gt;" で始まる従来のプレーンテキスト形式の引用。グラフィカルな引用では、境界線の色や配置、スタイルが調整できます。\n\nさらに、メッセージのテキスト色、背景色、リンク色、署名の色などの基本的な表示オプションを設定できます。',
     es:
      'Quote Colors es un complemento para Thunderbird y para el cliente de correo y noticias de SeaMonkey.\n\nPermite asignar el color del texto y el fondo para las citas de diferentes niveles al leer o imprimir mensajes de correo y noticias. Es posible configurar cinco niveles con diferentes colores.\nPuede elegir entre dos modos de visualización: citas gráficas con barras de colores alrededor de los párrafos (por defecto), y citas de texto plano tradicional donde cada línea de la cita comienza con uno más caracteres "&gt;". Para las citas gráficas es posible ajustar el color, la posición y el estilo de las barras.\n\nAdicionalmente, este complemento permite establecer algunas opciones básicas, como los colores para el texto, fondo, enlaces y firmas.' },

However, colors can be applied to HTML messages, but the result depends on the actual message. This way you can quickly send an email to all reciepients sorted to a folder - like friends or project participants, etc.\n\nYou can specify if "EMail Address Crawler" should search in the TO, FROM or CC field. And how often he needs to find an address before he adds it.\n\nIf there are several different formats, he will choose the one most complete:\n"Full Name email@address.org"   is preferred over \n"Name email@address.org"  which is preferred over\nemail@address.org\n\nFind e-mail addresses of long forgotten friends or easily create mailing lists for large groups.\n\nCySlider',

Normally, Thunderbird won\'t download message headers (let alone bodies) until the folder they\'re in is opened.\n\nAs an additional benefit, this keeps Saved Search folders up-to-date in IMAP accounts even if "search online" isn\'t checked.  Very handy if you have a Saved Search configured to show all of your unread email.' },

It asks a few question and then pre-compiles an email for you which you can review, change (if you want to) and send.   description:
   { 'en-US':
      'Prevents Thunderbird from selecting the next message after you\'ve deleted or moved the previously selected ones.  Stay in control of which message you want to have selected and displayed in the preview pane; that piece of spam you\'re deleting really shouldn\'t have a say in that.\n\nIn addition, you can click into the empty space below the last message in the thread list to unselect the currently selected message and to clear the preview pane.\n\nThis extension works best with the "Remember the last selected message" option unchecked.    { 'en-US':
      'This is an extension that reports, when possible, whether the sender shown in the From: header was actually the sender of the email. In fact, forging the From: address is possible! This is intended to be a tool to identify phishing attacks, fraudulent emails asking for your sensitive data, so that you don\'t fall prey. The extension uses Sender Policy Framework (SPF) (albeit in a nonstandard way) to verify the sending domain and SURBL, Spamhaus, DNSWL, and SenderScoreCertified for reputation information on the domain.' },
  developer_comments:
   { 'en-US':
      'BE AWARE: Please be sure to read about the extension on the extension\'s website (<a rel="nofollow" href="https://outgoing.prod.mozaws.net/v1/c0d748e8289a10fe8bcec48d9c6ea63ec734cbeed2709add2d91b33954753531/http%3A//razor.occams.info/code/spf">http://razor.occams.info/code/spf</a>) so you know what the extension is actually protecting you against, and how it works.  Not all emails can be verified, so don\'t be surprised if the extension has nothing to report for most of your email.  When you see an email *is* verified, then you can have more, but not complete, confidence in its authenticity.\n\nCritics say the extension uses SPF improperly by comparing the From: address of emails, rather than the return path, against SPF records.  it\'s really besides the point, so don\'t worry about that.\n\nMany have suggested checking the Received-SPF and Authentication-Results mail headers.  There\'s no way to know if these headers have been inserted by your ISP or by the malicious phisher, so the extension simply ignores them.' },

      'This extension makes hot keys work with Russian and Ukrainian "йцукен" keyboard layouts in Linux and *BSD (needed only for GTK2 builds). Don\'t try it with other languages/layouts, the result will be unpredictable. The problem with hot keys is well known to all Russian Mozilla users, it was reported over 6 years ago (bug #69230) but is fixed only in Firefox 3 beta 2. The extension is a hack, but it solves the problem for previous versions.\n\nSince 1.4 there is also experimental support for Hebrew and Russian/Ukrainian Dvorak layouts. Hebrew should work out-of-the-box (except keys with "Q" and "W"). To activate Dvorak mode go to about:config and specify integer "extensions.rhkbf.layout" preference (create it if it does not exist). The values are: "0" for Cyrillic and Hebrew "йцукен" (default) and "2" for Cyrillic Dvorak.' },

Clicking on a notification will focus Chatzilla.\n\nYou can turn off these notifications by changing what notifications Growl displays in the Growl prefpane.\n\nOnce you install and restart your browser, you should get a Growl notification indicating that the application has registered.\n\nIf you want some other extension to have Growl Notifications support, contact them and point them to this page: <a rel="nofollow" href="https://outgoing.prod.mozaws.net/v1/161eaccb0004f8139ccc160c0000f15b2226037a062a87e30075995266e90e2f/http%3A//trac.growl.info/wiki/MozillaGrowlNotifications">http://trac.growl.info/wiki/MozillaGrowlNotifications</a>',

      'Es ist nun möglich, Benachrichtigungen über Growl zu bekommen, wenn in Firefox ein Download startet, fertiggestellt ist, ein Fehler aufgetreten ist, oder dieser abgebrochen wurde. Durch anklicken wird das Thunderbird Fenster fokussiert.\n\nWenn Chatzilla installiert ist, können diverse Nachrichten rund um IRC angezeigt werden. However, the senders may not be aware that some of their email attachments actually contain sensitive or personal information which should not be revealed to their recipients. This creates a potential problem of confidential data leakage. \n\nOn the other hand, even the sender is aware of this it is still inconvenient and time-consuming to make a copy for each sensitive document and to remove those confidential contents in the copy before sending it. Therefore there is a demand for the email clients to handle such documents in a secure way.\n\n<strong>Our solutions</strong>\nWe provide a Thunderbird add-on called "Sensitive Attachment Guard" which is able to detect the existence of sensitive information in the email attachments (for Word 2007 and Excel 2007 documents only) and to notify the sender accordingly.    { 'en-US':
      'NotTo, as the title says, enables you to avoid sending mail to specific recipients.\n\nThe extension works in two levels:\n\n1. When you compose the mail you can mark an address to be NotTo address by selecting "NotTo" from the drop down box next to the addresses box.\nWhen sending the mail, the mail wouldn\'t be send to the addresses you\'ve specified. This is useful when you have a mailing list containing a lot of recipients and you wish to avoid sending the mail to specific individuals.\n\n2. A new forward command is added to the forward menu button: "NotTo Forward". It acts as regular forward, but in addition puts the sender in a NotTo address. This is useful when you want to forward a mail to a mailing list (like friends) which includes the original sender. You wouldn\'t want sending him back his mail.\n\nAcknowledgments goes to Noa Rotstein for this idea.' },

      'Problem: The Personas extension adds a background image to the toolbars at the top and status bar at the bottom, but it does not show through the status bar when using the Default application theme with the Windows Classic desktop theme (the only desktop theme on Windows 2000).  To see which application theme you have set, go to Tools (menu) ⇒ Add-ons ⇒ Themes (tab).  If the operating system is Windows XP or later, then to see which desktop theme is set, go to desktop ⇒ context menu (right-click) ⇒ Properties ⇒ Themes (tab).\n\nSolution: Personas Windows Classic Statusbar modifies the status bar style so the Persona footer background can show through.  <strong>Requires "Personas Plus" add-on extension ≤1.5.*.</strong>\n<a rel="nofollow" href="https://addons.mozilla.org/en-US/firefox/addon/personas-plus/versions/">https://addons.mozilla.org/en-US/firefox/addon/personas-plus/versions/</a>\n<a rel="nofollow" href="https://addons.mozilla.org/en-US/thunderbird/addon/personas-plus/versions/">https://addons.mozilla.org/en-US/thunderbird/addon/personas-plus/versions/</a>\n<a rel="nofollow" href="https://outgoing.prod.mozaws.net/v1/4ea3be30b1f3003c2592801e96d9e378a18b10069f02c17d63b2bcdc8a6a21f8/http%3A//www.getpersonas.com/">http://www.getpersonas.com/</a>\n\n(For an experimental add-on, when a new version is released, <code><a rel="nofollow" href="http://addons.mozilla.org">addons.mozilla.org</a></code> does not notify you from the application.   developer_comments:
   { 'en-US':
      'The problem is as follows: In the “Default” theme of a Mozilla application, the <code>-moz-appearance: statusbar</code> rule sets the background color, borders, and margins of statusbar panels to match the operating system desktop theme.  The <code>-moz-appearance</code> CSS rules, which make an element style match the host operating system desktop theme, cannot be partially overridden.  Therefore, Personas can\'t override the background of the statusbar panels without also removing their borders and margins matching the theme.\n\n<a rel="nofollow" href="https://outgoing.prod.mozaws.net/v1/fa97a573c58f3956548a6c72b1963af2089d674aeab7721917f4273eba34a75c/https%3A//bugzilla.mozilla.org/show_bug.cgi%3Fid=487711" title="Support alternate OS themes">Bug 487711</a> indicates that the Personas developers are reluctant to introduce and maintain fixes specific to individual themes, and would rather take fixes that work for all themes, such as allowing <code>-moz-appearance</code> rules to be partially overridden.  Such a fix might appear in future versions of the Mozilla platform. In the meantime...\n\nThis extension implements a fix specific to the Windows Classic theme.  It finds the current theme preference at start-up, and adds a theme property to the status bar so its CSS rules apply only if the <code>classic/1.0</code> theme is in use.  Its CSS rules add borders and margins similar to the effect of <code>-moz-appearance</code> rules for the Windows Classic theme, leaving the background open for the Persona.',
     ja:
      '問題は次：モジラのアプリケーションの｢デフォルト」テーマには, <code>-moz-appearance: statusbar</code> はオペレーティング・システムのデスクトップのテーマに調和するために、statusbar-panel のバックグラウンド色と境界とマージンを置きます。<code>-moz-appearance</code> CSS は、オペレーティング・システムのデスクトップのテーマと調和するために、エレメントのスタイルを置きますが、部分的に威圧できません。だからペルソナはステータス・バーのテーマに調和している境界とマージンを取り去らないでバックグラウンドを威圧できません。\n\n<a rel="nofollow" href="https://outgoing.prod.mozaws.net/v1/fa97a573c58f3956548a6c72b1963af2089d674aeab7721917f4273eba34a75c/https%3A//bugzilla.mozilla.org/show_bug.cgi%3Fid=487711" title="Support alternate OS themes">バグ４８７７１１</a>に、ペルソナの開発者は、一つばかりのテーマの解決を取り入れて維持することは悪いようです。<code>-moz-appearance</code> CSS を部分的に威圧できるような、すべてのテーマの解決のほうはいいです。 未来のモジラ・プラットフォームにそのような解決が出るかもしれません。この間に・・・\n\nこのアドオンは、Windows Classicテーマの解決ばかりを実行します。アプリケーションの始に、使っているアプリケーション・テーマを探して、<code>classic/1.0</code> のテーマを使っていればこのアドオンのCSSが使われてために、ステータスバーのエレメントにテーマの名前を付加します。この CSS は、Windows Classicのテーマの <code>-moz-appearance</code> のように境界とマージンを付加して、ペルソナのためにバックグラウンドを開いております。' },

Seleccione la opción "Gmail IMAP" para configurar el acceso imap de Gmail; "Gmail IMAP (Aplicaciones Google" para una cuenta de este tipo. Esta extensión realiza las siguientes acciones:\n\n* crea la nueva cuenta\n* configura el servidor SMTP\n* sincroniza las carpetas de borradores, enviados, spam, destacados y papelera\n* ajusta varias opciones para mejorar el rendimiento de Thunderbird\n\nLos ajustes están basados en las recomendaciones de Google. Consulte el siguiente enlace para más información:\n<a rel="nofollow" href="https://outgoing.prod.mozaws.net/v1/0aab68c8dcc8e2d11301c8d2a638e46da5e702203144d198699254eb7e8b6197/http%3A//mail.google.com/support/bin/answer.py%3Fanswer=78892&amp;topic=12761&amp;hl=en%23">http://mail.google.com/support/bin/answer.py?answer=78892&amp;topic=12761&amp;hl=en#</a>\n\nTenga en cuenta que la sincronización entre las carpetas especiales puede fallar si Gmail y Thunderbird usan idiomas diferentes o su idioma no está incluido en el paquete.\nConsulte el siguiente enlace para ver los idiomas incluidos: <a rel="nofollow" href="https://outgoing.prod.mozaws.net/v1/d93b35b5d554f6eb0e0d2a99c6afef8bba61d078f3ebe431b8099cf3c9f4d791/http%3A//hogiblog.blogspot.com/2007/11/call-for-translation.html">http://hogiblog.blogspot.com/2007/11/call-for-translation.html</a>\n\nHe creado otra extensión que sincroniza los contactos de Google y las libretas de direcciones de Thunderbird, llamada "Google Contacts". Creo que con ella podrá usar Gmail IMAP de un mejor modo. Por favor, pruébela. Puede descargarla desde los siguientes sitios:\n\n* AMO\n<a rel="nofollow" href="https://addons.mozilla.org/ja/thunderbird/addon/7307">https://addons.mozilla.org/ja/thunderbird/addon/7307</a>\n* mi página web\n<a rel="nofollow" href="https://outgoing.prod.mozaws.net/v1/11fcc7414712e469a0df685fd1fad7afd52c61b14985ddf04567303bcf322968/http%3A//hogi.a.orn.jp/en/">http://hogi.a.orn.jp/en/</a>' },

   { 'en-US':
      'Version 0.9:\nAdds a simple task list to print layouts and the ability to include tasks in MonthGrid and WeekGrid. [5]\n\nUp to version 0.2:\nThis extension was created to make Lightning look more like Sunbird...\n\nThere are 4 options you can choose:\n\n1. Move MiniMonthPick (small calendar in sidebar) to its own tab to conserve vertical space. (as requested in [1])\n\n2. Hide buttons (new, edit, delete) on calendar tab in sidebar to conserve horizontal space (they are not needed, as these functions are available in context menu and rarely used).\nThese buttons will be completely removed in future versions of Lightning\n\n3. Use UnifinderToDo (from Sunbird) to replace Lighning ToDo list. (as requested in [2])\nThis one is more functional looks better ;-)\n\n4. Use Unifinder (from Sunbird) to display an event list on top of the calendar view. (as requested in [3])\nThis is the only way to get a list of all events in Lightning 0.3.1 - in 0.5 you can print, but not display an event list.\nFor this to work, you have to modify 2 lines in \'messenger-overlay-sidebar.xul\' and \'messenger-overlay-sidebar.js\' (see Bug 386714, [4]).\n\nThere are still some bugs, I was not able to fix until now:\n- make Unifinder work without changes to Lightning\n- SelectAll in Unifinder event list only works in month-view\n- I was unable to change the context-menu of calendar views to Sunbird\'s\n\nIt was tested with Lightning 0.3.1, 0.5 and nightly builds up to build 2007070304 on Windows XP SP2 and Thunderbird 1.5 and 2.0.0.4.\n\nPlease feel free to report any errors or comments!\n\n[1] <a rel="nofollow" href="https://outgoing.prod.mozaws.net/v1/6152b5e983b9da859d6d1caa92bba0b59f192507af587d1d3cc2c98dd85ab7a8/https%3A//bugzilla.mozilla.org/show_bug.cgi%3Fid=372833">https://bugzilla.mozilla.org/show_bug.cgi?id=372833</a>\n[2] <a rel="nofollow" href="https://outgoing.prod.mozaws.net/v1/e5aade8c73a0df2332227e93a34d2d1fc2792520867f6545bb9f5bcdd177bec4/https%3A//bugzilla.mozilla.org/show_bug.cgi%3Fid=372830">https://bugzilla.mozilla.org/show_bug.cgi?id=372830</a>\n[3] <a rel="nofollow" href="https://outgoing.prod.mozaws.net/v1/6cdccb06a58af3fd5cb6151aa01d2ea70d8f93768b1cb0f5681627eafaa15438/https%3A//bugzilla.mozilla.org/show_bug.cgi%3Fid=372829">https://bugzilla.mozilla.org/show_bug.cgi?id=372829</a>\n[4] <a rel="nofollow" href="https://outgoing.prod.mozaws.net/v1/2bec4a08a249159c8c5030257e8d49f14b7db487ef091996d37d4618af190a73/https%3A//bugzilla.mozilla.org/show_bug.cgi%3Fid=386714">https://bugzilla.mozilla.org/show_bug.cgi?id=386714</a>\n\n[5] <a rel="nofollow" href="https://outgoing.prod.mozaws.net/v1/4a1225ff4c20e1acc674a54bc4f420e6d4cd89a85df47c8208402db368459c48/https%3A//bugzilla.mozilla.org/show_bug.cgi%3Fid=325137">https://bugzilla.mozilla.org/show_bug.cgi?id=325137</a>',

      'Version 0.9:\nFügt eine einfache Aufgabenliste als Drucklayout hinzu und ermöglicht den Ausdruck von Aufgaben in der Monatsübersicht und Wochenplanung. [5]\n\nBis Version 0.2:\nDiese Erweiterung wurde geschrieben, um Lightning mehr nach Sunbird aussehen zu lassen...\n\nEs gibt 4 einstellbare Optionen:\n\n1. MiniMonthPick (Monatskalender) in ein eigenes Tab im Tabpanel verschieben, um den vertikalen Platzbedarf zu reduzieren (wie in [1] gefordert)\n\n2. Schaltflächen auf dem Kalender-Tab (Neu, Bearbeiten, Löschen) verstecken, um den horizontalen Platzbedarf zu reduzieren (da diese auch im Kontextmenü verfügbar sind und eher selten benutzt werden)\nDiese Schaltflächen werden in zukünftigen Versionen von Lightning ohnehin entfernt.\n\n\n3. UnifinderToDo (aus Sunbird) als Ersatz für die Lightning ToDo-Liste benutzen (wie in [2] gefordert)\nDieses hat mehr Funktionen und sieht besser aus ;-)\n\n4. Unifinder (aus Sunbird) benutzen, um eine Terminliste oberhalb der Kalender Ansicht anzuzeigen. (wie in [3] gefordert)\nDas ist die einzige Möglichkeit, in Lightning 0.3.1 eine Liste aller Termine zu erhalten - in Lightning 0.5 kann diese ausgedruckt, aber nicht angezeigt werden.\nUm diese Funktion zu erhalten, müssen 2 Zeilen in den Dateien \'messenger-overlay-sidebar.xul\' und \'messenger-overlay-sidebar.js\' geändert werden (vgl. Bug 386714, [4]).\n\nLeider sind immer noch einige Bugs enthalten, die ich bisher nicht lösen konnte:\n- Unifinder ohne Änderungen an Lightning zu integrieren\n- "Alles markieren" im Unifinder funktioniert nur in der Monatsansicht\n- das Kontextmenü der Kalenderansicht konnte ich bisher nicht nachträglich auf das von Sunbird ändern\n\nDie Erweiterung wurde unter Lightning 0.3.1, 0.5 und den Nightly-Builds bis 2007070304 unter Windows XP SP2 und Thunderbird 1.5 und 2.0.0.4 getestet.\n\nJede Art von Kommentar oder Fehlermeldung ist willkommen!\n\n[1] <a rel="nofollow" href="https://outgoing.prod.mozaws.net/v1/6152b5e983b9da859d6d1caa92bba0b59f192507af587d1d3cc2c98dd85ab7a8/https%3A//bugzilla.mozilla.org/show_bug.cgi%3Fid=372833">https://bugzilla.mozilla.org/show_bug.cgi?id=372833</a>\n[2] <a rel="nofollow" href="https://outgoing.prod.mozaws.net/v1/e5aade8c73a0df2332227e93a34d2d1fc2792520867f6545bb9f5bcdd177bec4/https%3A//bugzilla.mozilla.org/show_bug.cgi%3Fid=372830">https://bugzilla.mozilla.org/show_bug.cgi?id=372830</a>\n[3] <a rel="nofollow" href="https://outgoing.prod.mozaws.net/v1/6cdccb06a58af3fd5cb6151aa01d2ea70d8f93768b1cb0f5681627eafaa15438/https%3A//bugzilla.mozilla.org/show_bug.cgi%3Fid=372829">https://bugzilla.mozilla.org/show_bug.cgi?id=372829</a>\n[4] <a rel="nofollow" href="https://outgoing.prod.mozaws.net/v1/2bec4a08a249159c8c5030257e8d49f14b7db487ef091996d37d4618af190a73/https%3A//bugzilla.mozilla.org/show_bug.cgi%3Fid=386714">https://bugzilla.mozilla.org/show_bug.cgi?id=386714</a>\n\n[5] <a rel="nofollow" href="https://outgoing.prod.mozaws.net/v1/4a1225ff4c20e1acc674a54bc4f420e6d4cd89a85df47c8208402db368459c48/https%3A//bugzilla.mozilla.org/show_bug.cgi%3Fid=325137">https://bugzilla.mozilla.org/show_bug.cgi?id=325137</a>' },
